.. table:: Serial Ports Nodes on the System
   :align: center
   :width: 100%
   :widths: auto

   +-----------------------------+-------------------------------+
   | Ports                       | Device Node                   |
   +=============================+===============================+
   | COM1(RS232, Debug)          | /dev/ttymxc0                  |
   +-----------------------------+-------------------------------+
   | COM2(RS485)                 | /dev/ttymxc1                  |
   +-----------------------------+-------------------------------+
   | COM3(RS232)                 | /dev/ttymxc2                  |
   +-----------------------------+-------------------------------+
   | COM4(RS485)                 | /dev/ttymxc3                  |
   +-----------------------------+-------------------------------+
   | COM5(RS485)                 | /dev/ttymxc4                  |
   +-----------------------------+-------------------------------+

.. note::

    If you use COM2(RS485), you canâ€™t use Bluetooth because COM2(RS485) share pin with Bluetooth.